s in their own social work practice. The guide features the perspectives of people with lived experience throughout and includes the following key learning features: • case studies of best practice; • points for practice: succinct tips for practitioners and students on practice placement; • further reading list and resources; • glossary.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSocial service. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aBailey, Lauren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdmondson, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Deanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Deanna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFleming, Mhairi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, Simone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGolden, Will, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMyers, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParkinson, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParkinson, Kate, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPollock, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRogers, Michaela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShennan, Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeygang, Emily, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWithers, Alex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-